hopobject.body: Could you tell me the number for ? healthylivinghowto.com That focus on a real-time photo stream was again highlighted with the release of Facebook's own Camera application for iOS devices in May of last year. Unlike Facebook's primary mobile app (which you can also use to take and share photos), Facebook Camera is only concerned with photo taking and photo sharing. Yet another example is the Photo Sync feature introduced last fall. With it enabled (it's a rare opt-in option for Facebook), every photo you take on your phone is automatically uploaded to a private album on Facebook (much like Apple's Photo Stream), from which you can then choose to publicly share photos with your friends.
